This paper deals with visual attention and neural networks, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The use of large-scale computational experiments suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the study of attention and perception also has implications for human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
